{
  "abstract": "GENSTAT programs for Hayman's approach of diallel analysis in two parts have been developed. The first program will \r\ncarryout the analysis of variance. In this technique, the total sum of squares is partitioned into various components, namely a (additive), b (non-additive, wich is further sub-divided into b1, b2 and b3), c (maternal) and d (reciprocal differences other than C).",
